    "roleHeading": "Sample Code",
    "title": "Tracking specific points in world space"
  },
  "primaryContentSections": [
    {
      "content": [
        {
          "anchor": "Overview",
          "level": 2,
          "text": "Overview",
          "type": "heading"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "text": "Use world anchors along with an ARKit session’s ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/ARKit/WorldTrackingProvider",
              "isActive": true,
              "type": "reference"
            },
            {
              "text": " to track points of interest in the world over time, as a person moves while wearing the device, and across device usage sessions. For example, someone might place a 3D object in a specific position on their desk and expect it to come back the next time they use the device.",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "identifier": "world-tracking.mp4",
          "type": "video"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "text": "ARKit keeps track of a unique identifier for each world anchor your app creates and automatically places those anchors back in the space when the person returns to your app in the same location. A world tracking provider also provides the position of the device the person is wearing.",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "anchor": "Start-an-ARKit-session-with-world-tracking",
          "level": 3,
          "text": "Start an ARKit session with world tracking",
          "type": "heading"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "text": "Use an ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/ARKit/ARKitSession",
              "isActive": true,
              "type": "reference"
            },
            {
              "text": " configured for world tracking to start receiving updates on the world anchors your app places. The following shows updates to world anchors your app previously registered using the ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/ARKit/WorldTrackingProvider/addAnchor(_:)",
              "isActive": true,
              "type": "reference"
            },
            {
              "text": " method:",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "code": [
            "let session = ARKitSession()",
            "let worldInfo = WorldTrackingProvider()",
            "",
            "Task {",
            "    try await session.run([worldInfo])",
            "    ",
            "    for await update in worldInfo.anchorUpdates {",
            "        switch update.event {",
            "        case .added, .updated:",
            "            // Update the app's understanding of this world anchor.",
            "            print(\"Anchor position updated.\")",
            "        case .removed:",
            "            // Remove content related to this anchor.",
            "            print(\"Anchor position now unknown.\")",
            "    }",
            "}"
          ],
          "syntax": "swift",
          "type": "codeListing"
        },
        {
          "content": [
            {
              "inlineContent": [
                {
                  "text": "If a person repositions the current space — for example, by holding down the Digital Crown — world anchor updates begin updating their position relative to the new world origin. For example, a world anchor placed on a table still reports information about the table’s position, but those positions are relative to the updated world origin.",
                  "type": "text"
                }
              ],
              "type": "paragraph"
            }
          ],
          "name": "Important",
          "style": "important",
          "type": "aside"
        },
        {
          "anchor": "Create-and-add-world-anchors",
          "level": 3,
          "text": "Create and add world anchors",
          "type": "heading"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "text": "You can create world anchors for any point of interest in your app’s world coordinate system once you’ve started a world tracking ARKit session. For example, you might track that a person placed an item at a particular offset from a desk in their space:",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "code": [
            "let anchor = WorldAnchor(originFromAnchorTransform: deskPlane.originFromAnchorTransform + offset)",
            "try await worldInfo.addAnchor(anchor)"
          ],
          "syntax": "swift",
          "type": "codeListing"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "text": "Once you add a world anchor to your app’s tracking provider using the ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/ARKit/WorldTrackingProvider/addAnchor(_:)",
              "isActive": true,
              "type": "reference"
            },
            {
              "text": " method, the ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/ARKit/WorldTrackingProvider/anchorUpdates",
              "isActive": true,
              "type": "reference"
            },
            {
              "text": " sequence in the current session and future runs of your app provides updates to the current position of that new world anchor.",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "anchor": "Persist-world-anchors-across-sessions",
          "level": 3,
          "text": "Persist world anchors across sessions",
          "type": "heading"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "text": "The only information ARKit persists about the world anchors in your app is their ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/foundation/uuid",
              "isActive": true,
              "type": "reference"
            },
            {
              "text": " — a ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/ARKit/WorldAnchor",
              "isActive": true,
              "type": "reference"
            },
            {
              "text": " instance’s ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/ARKit/WorldAnchor/id",
              "isActive": true,
              "type": "reference"
            },
            {
              "text": " property — and pose in a particular space. It’s your app’s responsibility to persist additional information, such as the meaning of each anchor. For example, you might save local data about a custom 3D lamp model that a person placed on their desk.",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "text": "As a person moves from town-to-town or room-to-room, your app won’t receive all of the world anchor updates from each place someone used your app. Instead, the ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/ARKit/WorldTrackingProvider/anchorUpdates",
              "isActive": true,
              "type": "reference"
            },
            {
              "text": " sequence only provides world anchors for nearby objects.",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "anchor": "Track-the-device-position-in-the-world",
          "level": 3,
          "text": "Track the device position in the world",
          "type": "heading"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "text": "Use the Compositor Services framework and the ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/ARKit/WorldTrackingProvider",
              "isActive": true,
              "type": "reference"
            },
            {
              "text": " class’s ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/ARKit/WorldTrackingProvider/queryDeviceAnchor(atTimestamp:)",
              "isActive": true,
              "type": "reference"
            },
            {
              "text": " method to get low-latency information about the current and future-predicted pose of the person’s device in world space. For more information, see ",
              "type": "text"
            },
            {
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/CompositorServices/drawing-fully-immersive-content-using-metal",
              "isActive": true,
              "type": "reference"
            },
            {
              "text": ".",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ],
          "type": "paragraph"
        }
      ],
      "kind": "content"
    }
  ],
